HEADWORD: Water gang
<hw>Wa"ter gang`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>. <fld>(O. E. Law)</fld> <def>A
passage for water, such as was usually made in a sea wall, to drain
water out of marshes.</def> <rj><au>Burrill.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Water gas</ent>⟦br⟧
